First Lady Michelle Obama released her first-ever Spotify playlist in honor of International Day of the Girl. The playlist features songs that inspire and empower girls. In an interview with Hercampus, Michelle Obama discussed her girls' education initiative, Let Girls Learn. The initiative aims to help adolescent girls around the world overcome barriers to education, such as lack of resources and cultural beliefs. She encouraged young women in the US to raise awareness about this issue and get involved in Let Girls Learn. Michelle Obama also shared her own experience with education and the importance of seeking help when needed. Lastly, she mentioned that her current favorite song is from the soundtrack of Hamilton.